Name: hepatic coma
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of animals and humans by nematodes of the superfamily Trichostrongyloidea.

Name: obsolete Escherichia coli septicemia
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of animals and humans by nematodes of the superfamily Trichostrongyloidea.
Synonym: Septicemia due to escherichia coli [E. coli]
